Bootstraps a project scaffolded from the CTX template by building the `ctx-*` tool binaries from a sibling CTX tooling repo and copying them plus their summarizer prompts into the local project, so hooks and `CLAUDE.md` (which reference `target/debug/ctx-*` by fixed relative path) work immediately after copying `template/`.

Locates the CTX repo via arg `$1`, else `$CTX_REPO` env var, else `../CTX`; fails fast if `crates/ctx-context/Cargo.toml` isn't found there. Builds five cargo packages (`ctx-context ctx-scan ctx-verify ctx-cage ctx-summarize`) but copies six binaries — `ctx-cage`'s package emits both `ctx-cage` and `ctx-run`, so `PACKAGES` and `BINARIES` arrays intentionally differ in length/contents; keep them in sync if the tooling repo adds/renames binaries. Binaries are copied from the tooling repo's `target/debug/` into this project's `target/debug/`, not symlinked, so re-running is required whenever the tooling repo rebuilds. Also copies `summarizer-leaf.md` and `summarizer-rollup.md` from the tooling repo's `prompts/` into local `./prompts/`, since `ctx-scan`/`ctx-summarize` resolve that path relative to cwd at runtime, not relative to their own binary location. Every run overwrites prior binaries and prompts unconditionally — no version check or skip-if-unchanged logic.